  "prompt": "Does every student at iiser get fellowship?",
  "response": "At IISER (Indian Institutes of Science Education and Research), not every student receives a fellowship. The fellowship availability depends on several factors:\n\n1. PhD Students:\n- Most PhD students receive a fellowship/stipend\n- Typically, they get a monthly fellowship from agencies like CSIR, UGC, or INSPIRE\n- The amount ranges from \u20b925,000 to \u20b935,000 per month\n\n2. Integrated MSc Students:\n- Some students may receive scholarships or fellowships\n- Not all students automatically get a fellowship\n- Selection depends on merit, performance, and availability of funds\n\n3. Selection Criteria for Fellowships:\n- Academic performance\n- Qualifying in national-level entrance exams\n- Availability of research funding\n- Institute's discretion\n\n4. Types of Fellowships:\n- CSIR-NET fellowship\n- UGC-NET fellowship\n- INSPIRE fellowship\n- Institute-specific scholarships\n\n5. Recommendation:\n- Students should check specific details with individual IISER campuses\n- Eligibility and fellowship conditions can vary\n\nWhile many students do receive fellowships, it's not guaranteed for every student at IISER.",
